  "doc_id": "39441",
  "text": "Among the studies that involve the application of metaheuristics for the unrelated PMSP with sequence and machine dependent setup time, [CITATION_1] solved the problem with the aim of reducing the total weighed tardiness. The authors considered a dynamic task expedition and a dynamic availability of machines in order to approximate the real situation problem of several industries. Six types of algorithms based on taboo search were implemented. [CITATION_2] applied a metaheuristics based on GRASP (Greedy Randomized Adaptive Search Procedure) to reduce makespan and weighed delays. [CITATION_3] used a Variable Neighborhood Search Algorithm (VNS) with the aim of reducing the makespan and weighed delays. [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] proposed a genetic algorithm to reduce the makespan sequencing. [CITATION_6] reported five hybrid metaheuristics to solve the problem by reducing the makespan: three hybrid algorithms by ant colony and two hybrid simulated annealing algorithms.",
